ROGUE TRADER
============
Real-time multiplayer trading game disguised as an Excel spreadsheet.
Wall Street never closes. Neither do you.

WHAT'S IN THIS FOLDER
---------------------
- server.py         -- Python backend (Flask + WebSocket)
- index.html        -- Frontend (single-file, mobile-first Excel clone)
- requirements.txt  -- Python dependencies
- README.txt        -- This file

QUICK START (LOCAL)
-------------------
1. Install Python 3.10+
2. Open terminal in this folder
3. Run:
     pip install -r requirements.txt
     python server.py
4. Open browser: http://localhost:5000
5. Enter a trader name and start playing

DEPLOY OPTIONS
--------------

Option A: Railway.app (easiest, free tier)
1. Push this folder to a GitHub repo
2. Go to railway.app, connect your repo
3. Set start command: python server.py
4. Set PORT env variable (Railway auto-sets this)
5. Deploy. Share the URL with friends.
Option B: Render.com (free tier)
1. Push to GitHub
2. Create new Web Service on Render
3. Build command: pip install -r requirements.txt
4. Start command: python server.py
5. Deploy.

Option C: VPS (DigitalOcean, Linode, etc.)
1. SSH into your server
2. Clone the repo
3. pip install -r requirements.txt
4. python server.py &
5. Set up nginx reverse proxy to port 5000
6. Point your domain to the server IP

Option D: Docker
1. Create Dockerfile:
     FROM python:3.11-slim
     WORKDIR /app
     COPY . .
     RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
     EXPOSE 5000
     CMD ["python", "server.py"]
2. docker build -t rogue-trader .
3. docker run -p 5000:5000 rogue-trader

GAME MECHANICS
--------------
- Start with $50,000 cash- Monthly expenses: $5,000 (Airbnb + Uber + UberEats)
- Trade stocks, crypto, forex with 100x real-life volatility
- Bet on real sports teams (soccer, basketball, football, baseball)
- Black market deals: high risk, high reward, chance of getting busted
- Buy lifestyle items to reduce/increase expenses
- Buy businesses for passive income
- Global leaderboard tracks all players in real-time
- News events move prices — watch the ticker
- Real-time simulation: 1 real day = 1 game day

TECH STACK
----------
- Backend: Python 3 + Flask + Flask-SocketIO
- Frontend: Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS + Socket.IO client
- No database needed (in-memory state, resets on server restart)
- For persistence: add SQLite or Redis (future upgrade)

